            <div class="comment-head">
            By the male homemaker on <a href="#comment-61892" title="">October 2nd, 2008 at 5:17 am</a> 			</div>
            
            
			<p>For years I&#8217;ve been mixing 4 parts to 1, filtered tap water with a citrus acid/tartrazine based Lime concentrate, then add a pinch of salt.<br />
This is cheap, healthy and extremely refreshing on hot days.  The best things is my kids who swim competively love this drink and use it during work outs and races.</p>
<p>We&#8217;ve also used mixed into this concoction on extremely hot days when the kids compete, the cheap packs of dehydration powders they are easy to find in pharmacies.</p>
<p>This is a low in Calories, cheap, a bit sour but great tasting, healthy and cheap.</p>
            
